00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:25.300
segments in Nigeria.

00:19:25.300 --> 00:19:27.430
And these custom
segments are actually

00:19:27.430 --> 00:19:29.030
defined by their connectivity.

00:19:29.030 --> 00:19:31.180
So how they actually
connect to the internet more

00:19:31.180 --> 00:19:33.150
than anything else.

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:35.710
But looking at Nigeria
as a broad market.

00:19:35.710 --> 00:19:39.820
What is really interesting
from a social angle

00:19:39.820 --> 00:19:43.270
is-- I don't know if you guys
are familiar with Nollywood?

00:19:43.270 --> 00:19:45.850
It's the third
largest movie industry

00:19:45.850 --> 00:19:53.740
in the world behind Hollywood
and Bollywood, of course,

00:19:53.740 --> 00:19:55.390
from India.

00:19:55.390 --> 00:19:59.530
It's actually the second
largest contributor to our GDP

00:19:59.530 --> 00:20:01.420
after oil and gas.

00:20:01.420 --> 00:20:03.260
So huge employer of people.

00:20:03.260 --> 00:20:05.710
And the locals are
really, really keen

00:20:05.710 --> 00:20:08.350
on their local movies.

00:20:08.350 --> 00:20:10.489
Our music is actually
very huge exports.

00:20:10.489 --> 00:20:12.280
So there's a lot of
hip hop music coming up

00:20:12.280 --> 00:20:15.550
from Nigeria, which is
going across different parts

00:20:15.550 --> 00:20:17.717
of the continent in
Africa and overseas.

00:20:17.717 --> 00:20:19.300
Huge exports here
in the West as well.

00:20:19.300 --> 00:20:22.990
So when you go to clubs and
bars in most popular cities,

00:20:22.990 --> 00:20:26.740
you are more likely to come
across one of our musics.

00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:28.890
Football is huge.

00:20:28.890 --> 00:20:32.240
It's second to
religion in Nigeria.

00:20:32.240 --> 00:20:35.170
We are fanatics when
it comes to football.

00:20:35.170 --> 00:20:36.220
We love our premiership.

00:20:36.220 --> 00:20:38.410
We love our LaLiga.

00:20:38.410 --> 00:20:41.290
And you know, there was this
story about these two Nigerians

00:20:41.290 --> 00:20:44.570
who got into a massive
fight over which footballer

00:20:44.570 --> 00:20:46.320
was the best football
in the world, Lionel

00:20:46.320 --> 00:20:48.710
Messi or Cristiano Ronaldo.

00:20:48.710 --> 00:20:51.110
So we don't take
it very lightly.

00:20:51.110 --> 00:20:54.550
Religion, like I
said, is-- pretty

00:20:54.550 --> 00:20:59.020
much every street in
Nigeria has a church.

00:20:59.020 --> 00:21:03.350
So I watched a
little clip recently

00:21:03.350 --> 00:21:07.030
that showed that the top 10
richest pastors, depending

00:21:07.030 --> 00:21:09.640
on what denomination you
are, but the top 10 richest

00:21:09.640 --> 00:21:12.210
pastors in the world, 5
of them are Nigerians.

00:21:12.210 --> 00:21:14.410
Four of whom are
actually in Nigeria.

00:21:14.410 --> 00:21:18.550
So despite the fact that we do
have huge economic challenges,

00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:21.480
people are very generous
when it comes to church.

00:21:21.480 --> 00:21:24.340
And then, fashion is sort of
like becoming a modern trend.

00:21:24.340 --> 00:21:28.620
And there's huge adoption
for fashion design.

00:21:28.620 --> 00:21:33.220
People are very interested in
what they wear and are shopping

00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:34.830
for these kind of things.

00:21:34.830 --> 00:21:36.785
Politically, the way
the opportunities--

00:21:36.785 --> 00:21:39.160
I mean, this is kind of like
opportunities and challenges

00:21:39.160 --> 00:21:39.868
at the same time.

00:21:39.868 --> 00:21:41.440
But politically,
what the government

00:21:41.440 --> 00:21:44.046
is really interested
in is in education.

00:21:44.046 --> 00:21:46.170
So education is a huge
challenge for the continent.

00:21:46.170 --> 00:21:48.700
So any sort of apps
that enable people

00:21:48.700 --> 00:21:50.610
to learn on the go on
their mobile device

00:21:50.610 --> 00:21:52.289
is actually a very huge hit.

00:21:52.289 --> 00:21:53.830
And then, anything
around empowerment

00:21:53.830 --> 00:21:55.913
is also a very huge hit
because the government has

00:21:55.913 --> 00:21:58.780
a very large youth population.

00:21:58.780 --> 00:22:00.610
And getting these
people educated

00:22:00.610 --> 00:22:02.680
and giving them
access to employment,

00:22:02.680 --> 00:22:05.500
opportunities is actually
a huge challenge for them.

00:22:05.500 --> 00:22:09.910
On the mobile side, Nigeria has
huge infrastructure problems.

00:22:09.910 --> 00:22:14.800
So I actually came to
London via Cape Town.

00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:16.990
And in Cape Town,
they have-- in South,

00:22:16.990 --> 00:22:19.000
Africa they occasionally
have something

00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:21.580
called load shedding,
which is where

00:22:21.580 --> 00:22:25.540
people-- for a couple of hours
in the day, the government

00:22:25.540 --> 00:22:30.350
is distributing power
between different districts.

00:22:30.350 --> 00:22:32.230
It is possible for you
to actually lose power

00:22:32.230 --> 00:22:33.674
for a couple of hours in a day.

00:22:33.674 --> 00:22:35.590
In Nigeria, it's a
completely different thing.

00:22:35.590 --> 00:22:38.250
I mean, there's no such
thing as load shedding.

00:22:38.250 --> 00:22:40.480
It's just power outage.

00:22:40.480 --> 00:22:43.484
And this is probably about
80%, 90% of the time.

00:22:43.484 --> 00:22:45.150
For those of you
who've been to Nigeria,

00:22:45.150 --> 00:22:46.900
it's a huge, huge, huge problem.

00:22:46.900 --> 00:22:50.170
Which means that battery
life is actually hugely

00:22:50.170 --> 00:22:51.940
important to mobile users.

00:22:51.940 --> 00:22:54.070
Most people have
battery power packs

00:22:54.070 --> 00:22:55.870
that they use with
their mobile phones,

00:22:55.870 --> 00:22:58.350
but that is not sufficient.

00:22:58.350 --> 00:23:01.480
Internet, like Iky said
earlier, is extremely expensive.

00:23:01.480 --> 00:23:02.860
And that is
something that people

00:23:02.860 --> 00:23:04.245
are very conscious about.

00:23:04.245 --> 00:23:05.620
There's not a lot
of transparency

00:23:05.620 --> 00:23:07.030
between the internet
service providers

00:23:07.030 --> 00:23:09.040
and the actual end
consumers in terms of what

00:23:09.040 --> 00:23:10.400
their data is being used for.

00:23:10.400 --> 00:23:14.620
So you can buy a data
bundle of maybe 2 gigs

00:23:14.620 --> 00:23:16.510
and it can run out
in a couple of hours.

00:23:16.510 --> 00:23:18.587
And people don't have
a huge understanding

00:23:18.587 --> 00:23:20.170
as to how their data
is actually being

00:23:20.170 --> 00:23:23.740
utilized for the amount
of money they're paying.

00:23:23.740 --> 00:23:25.610
Free peer-to-peer
communication tools

00:23:25.610 --> 00:23:30.640
are massive because of
voice and data costs.

00:23:30.640 --> 00:23:33.490
So people adopt these
products to enable

00:23:33.490 --> 00:23:36.490
them to keep in touch
with friends and family.

00:23:36.490 --> 00:23:39.470
And then, internet connectivity
is another huge challenge.

00:23:39.470 --> 00:23:42.730
And this is around the
infrastructure difficulties

00:23:42.730 --> 00:23:45.506
for a lot of the telcos and
internet service providers

00:23:45.506 --> 00:23:46.130
in the country.

00:23:49.150 --> 00:23:51.520
I'm going to dive into the
different user segments.

00:23:51.520 --> 00:23:55.300
So earlier, I touched on
the four user segments.

00:23:55.300 --> 00:23:58.319
So if you're bringing
a product into Nigeria,

00:23:58.319 --> 00:23:59.860
looking at the
Nigerian market, these

00:23:59.860 --> 00:24:02.200
are four unique
categories of users

00:24:02.200 --> 00:24:03.910
based on their connectivity.

00:24:03.910 --> 00:24:10.180
So we have what we termed
as the always-on segment.

00:24:10.180 --> 00:24:14.290
Now, these guys are pretty
much the types of people

00:24:14.290 --> 00:24:17.034
that you would expect to
meet in any developed market.

00:24:17.034 --> 00:24:17.950
They're well-educated.

00:24:17.950 --> 00:24:20.730
Most of them actually have some
level of foreign education.

00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:24.330
They're well-traveled.

00:24:24.330 --> 00:24:28.020
They earn a decent salary
by Nigeria standards.

00:24:28.020 --> 00:24:30.850
They connect to the internet
via multiple devices.

00:24:30.850 --> 00:24:33.760
What they really care about
is the connection speed more

00:24:33.760 --> 00:24:35.050
than price.

00:24:35.050 --> 00:24:38.080
They're not as price-sensitive.

00:24:38.080 --> 00:24:41.749
They access their content
via the app stores.

00:24:41.749 --> 00:24:44.040
They have multiple payment
options, so they can update.

00:24:44.040 --> 00:24:46.498
They're very comfortable paying
with credit cards and debit

00:24:46.498 --> 00:24:50.000
cards or using payment
platforms like PayPal

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:54.870
because they've lived abroad
and they understand the security

00:24:54.870 --> 00:24:58.680
benefits or the convenience
benefits of actually doing

00:24:58.680 --> 00:25:00.960
transactions online.

00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:05.430
You would find them using
apps like Uber, YouTube.

00:25:05.430 --> 00:25:08.340
They're huge video consumers.

00:25:08.340 --> 00:25:10.350
And they play games
that require you to be

